        "title": "Add Codex combined 5h and weekly percent option",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a narrow Codex-only option for issue #1294: an opt-in `Session + Weekly` menu bar metric for percent mode.\n\nThe compact menu bar label shows both Codex percentage windows together, for example:\n\n`5h 89% · W 80%`\n\n## Scope\n\n- Codex-only\n- Opt-in setting under the Codex provider menu bar metric picker\n- Percent mode renders both session and weekly percentages\n- Existing Automatic, Primary, and Secondary behavior remains unchanged\n- Falls back to the available lane if session or weekly is unavailable\n- Preserves the existing credits fallback when no percent lane is available or a visible Codex lane is exhausted\n- Uses the most constrained selected lane for shared menu-bar ranking, reset, and countdown consumers; existing Codex pace behavior remains unchanged\n- Keeps Codex eligible for highest-usage ranking while either selected lane still has quota\n- Includes maintainer changelog credit for @thepraggyverse\n- Documents the combined metric picker in `docs/ui.md`\n\nRefs #1294.\n\n## Validation\n\nExact head: `c7166f6a`\n\n- `swift test --filter 'CodexConsumerProjectionCharacterizationTests|StatusItemAnimationTests|SettingsStoreAdditionalTests|LocalizationLanguageCatalogTests|MenuBarMetricWindowResolverTests|UsageStoreHighestUsageTests|CodexCombinedMetricHighestUsageTests'` — passed on exact head\n- `make check` — passed; 0 formatting changes and 0 lint violations\n- `make test` — all 41 groups passed\n- `autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` — clean after fixing the partial-exhaustion ranking finding and supplying the explicit credits-fallback contract\n",
